0w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/The-Duskbloods-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/The-Duskbloods-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/The-Duskbloods-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/games/bloodborne"><em>Bloodborne</em></a> fans are very excited about the <a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/nintendo-switch-2">Switch 2</a> -exclusive game <em>The Duskbloods</em> , with many considering it a spiritual successor to the action fantasy title.</p><ul><li> <strong>READ MORE:</strong> <a href="https://www.nme.com/features/gaming-features/doom-the-dark-ages-preview-release-date-multiplayer-3831519">&#39;Doom: The Dark Ages&#39; is the most fun you&#39;ll have with a game this year</a></li></ul><p> Nintendo <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/gaming-news/nintendo-switch-2-release-date-price-pre-order-3851248">hosted an hour-long Direct yesterday</a> (April 2) that revealed a bunch of new information about the Switch 2, which is coming June 5.</p><p> A number of <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/gaming-news/switch-2-games-elden-ring-split-fiction-and-borderlands-4-3851267">iconic games were confirmed for the bigger, more powerful console</a> including <em><a href="https://www.nme.com/games/elden-ring">Elden Ring</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/games/split-fiction">Split Fiction</a></em> and <a href="https://www.nme.com/games/star-wars-outlaws"><em>Star Wars Outlaws</em></a> . A range of exclusive titles were also announced, with <em>Mario Kart World, Donkey Kong: Bananza</em> and <em><a href="https://www.nme.com/games/the-legend-of-zelda-tears-of-the-kingdom">The Legend Of Zelda: Tears Of The Kingdom</a></em> prequel <em>Hyrule Warriors: Age Of Imprisonment</em> set to be released later this year.</p><p> Perhaps the most surprising game announced during yesterday&#39;s Direct was <em>The Duskbloods</em> . Developed by FromSoftware&#39;s Hidetaka Miyazaki, <em>The Duskbloods</em> is a PvPvE title with “online multiplayer at its core” and up to eight players competing at once. It&#39;s set for release at some point in 2026. </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="The Duskbloods – Nintendo Direct | Nintendo Switch 2" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/niKHDEKQ7xA?feature=oembed&enablejsapi=1" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> However a number of fans believe <em>The Duskbloods</em> is a spiritual successor to Miyazaki&#39;s 2015 action fantasy game Bloodborne, and not just because of how often the trailer mentions the word “blood”.</p><p> “It&#39;s about as close to <em>Bloodborne 2</em> as you can get without legally calling it <em>Bloodborne</em> , as I&#39;m sure it&#39;s still tied up in Sony exclusivity,” one fan <a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/bloodborne/comments/1jpp8q0/comment/ml0xiyp/?utm_source=share&amp;utm_medium=web3x&amp;utm_name=web3xcss&amp;utm_term=1&amp;utm_content=share_button" target="_blank" rel="noopener">wrote</a> on Reddit with other fans convinced the trailer was advertising a new <em>Bloodborne</em> title on first watch. “The aesthetic is damn near identical, the clock tower looked the same and had the same chime, and they mentioned blood and the moon like 20 times,” <a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/bloodborne/comments/1jpp8q0/comment/ml0xhhm/?utm_source=share&amp;utm_medium=web3x&amp;utm_name=web3xcss&amp;utm_term=1&amp;utm_content=share_button" target="_blank" rel="noopener">said</a> another. Meanwhile on Twitter, a number of<a href="https://x.com/BustinTrudeau/status/1907437305293361636" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Bloodborne</em> -inspired memes</a> are being shared.</p><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550" data-dnt="true"><p lang="en" dir="ltr"> FromSoftware：“索尼可以做血态2”</p><p>索尼：“不”</p><p> FromSoftware: &quot;kk say less&quot; <a href="https://t.co/Py0wL99TUy">pic.twitter.com/Py0wL99TUy</a></p><p> — Radec (@realradec) <a href="https://twitter.com/realradec/status/1907431744141234208?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">April 2, 2025</a> </p></blockquote><p><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></p><p> The original Bloodborne was released in 2015 and took influence from the works of fantasy horror authors Bram Stoker and HP Lovecraft. The PlayStation 4-exclusive game went on to sell over 7million copies and is still considered one of the greatest video games ever made, but a sequel was never made. The game celebrated its tenth anniversary earlier this year and <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/gaming-news/bloodborne-remake-news-annoucement-release-date-3835526">fans were convinced Sony would announce a remaster</a> , especially after they <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/gaming-news/bloodborne-fans-think-30th-anniversary-playstation-video-hints-at-a-new-project-3818286">hinted something was coming</a> , but nothing has been confirmed yet.</p><p> <em>The Dusklands</em> wouldn&#39;t be the first time Miyazaki has created a spiritual successor to one of his games. 2011&#39;s <em><a href="https://www.nme.com/games/dark-souls">Dark Souls</a></em> was a loose follow-up to 2009&#39;s <a href="https://www.nme.com/games/demons-souls"><em>Demon&#39;s Souls</em></a> , which itself was the spiritual successor to FromSoftware&#39;s <em>King&#39;s Field</em> series. Miyazaki is set to share more information about <em>The Dusklands</em> tomorrow (April 4).</p><p> In other news, Nintendo has confirmed that the long-awaited <em><a href="https://www.nme.com/games/hollow-knight-silksong">Hollow Knight: Silksong</a></em> is <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/gaming-news/hollow-knight-silksong-release-date-2025-3851544">definitely coming out later this year.</a></p><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/gaming-news/bloodborne-2-the-duskbloods-switch-2-fromsoftware-3851572">&#39;Bloodborne&#39; fans very excited about new Switch game &#39;The Duskbloods&#39;: “Just call it &#39;Bloodborne 2&#39; bro”</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
